<p>Draft entries allow you to compose an entry in stages.  To create a draft entry, create an entry as normal but before submitting the entry, find <span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Publish Status</span> in the <span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Miscellaneous Options</span> on the lower section of the entry creation page. This option defaults to <span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Publish Now</span>.</p>

<p>Change <span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Publish Now</span> to <span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Draft</span> and then save. Alternatively, you may press the <span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Save Draft</span> button at any time.</p>

<p><span class="smallfont" style="font-weight:bold">Your Pending and Draft entries are only viewable by you until they are published.</span></p>